This paper deals with the generation and detection of Deepfake videos, which involves computer vision and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of generative adversarial networks (GANs) for creating Deepfakes, which falls under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also addresses the security and privacy concerns related to Deepfakes, which could be classified under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the vulnerability of face recognition systems to Deepfakes, which could be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
